title.narrative: 5.4 COMMUNITY ENGAGEMENT

description.narrative: 5.4 Participatory community engagement is strengthened to promote sustainable behavioral social change on key behaviours and social norms on integrated sector priorities, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Social And Behaviour Change, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Evaluation, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: 5. By the end of 2022, multidimensional child poverty in Lebanon is reduced with increased national and community level action for children

description.narrative: Communication for development (C4D) ensured strategic technical support to all programs and field offices to strengthen the capacity of partners, municipalities, and local stakeholders to promote the uptake of healthy and protective behaviors. In 2021 C4D particularly focused on supporting the COVID-19 pandemic response, leveraging from and expanding the existing community engagement platforms, and promoting RCCE plans and activities locally designed and implemented. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:15/12/2021
